            WHERE IS VCBW TAKING PLACE?












          VCBW will be taking place the PNE Fairgrounds at 2901 E. Hastings in Vancouver, BC.


















            REMIND ME THE BASIC DETAILS (DATE, TIME, ETC.)












          SATURDAY JULY 12, 202512PM-4PM (Afternoon Tasting)5PM - 9PM (Evening Tasting)THE CONCERTSThe MossOliver HazardHarbourTHE PRODUCTSCraft BeerCidersBC Natural WinesWings + Other Foods


















            HOW MUCH ARE TICKETS?












          Tickets start at their lowest price and as they sell and as the event gets closer, ticket prices increase.There are two categories of tickets: GA and GA+GA tickets start at $30 and will eventually end up at their regular price of $49, before selling out.GA+ tickets start at $55 and will eventually end up at their regular price of $74, before selling out. There are limited amount of GA+ tickets.


















            WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN GA AND GA+TICKETS AND WHAT IS INCLUDED IN EACH?












          GA TICKETAdmission During the Tasting its For (Aft vs. Eve)Souvenir Tasting CupThe ConcertsGA+ TICKETAll GA perks+*$30 Worth of Tokens*Private GA+ Entrance Private GA+ Bathrooms


















            IS THE EVENT RAIN OR SHINE?












          Yep!  We will be soaking up the rays of sun or frolicking within the drops of rain.


















            HOW DO TOKENS WORKS? HOW MUCH ARE SAMPLES?












          Each product is purchased at the event using the festival token. Tokens can be pre-purchased or purchased onsite.Most, if not all beverage samples at VCBW are about $2 (+tax) worth of tokens .Food is available for purchase on site using credit/debit cards.


















            HOW DO I GET ACCESS TO THE PRE-SALE WINDOWS, DISCOUNTED TICKETS AND VIP EVENTS?












          Make sure you are on the Feaster list.  This is where any and all of the above will be released. Sign up for the list on the VCBW website.


















            DO YOU SELL DESIGNATED DRIVER TICKETS?












          We do not have a different ticket available for DDs. We welcome designated drivers and have thus the ticket is now a-la-carte in that you are just purchasing admission and if you want to sample alcohol, you’d purchase tokens to do so. Purchasing a GA ticket also gives the DD access to many food items, the concerts, non-alc beverage samples and entertainment. DO NOT DRINK AND DRIVE!


















            WHEN CAN I BUY TICKETS TO VCBW?












          All tickets for this event are purchased through ticketleader.ca. Pre-sale begins after March!


















            DO I NEED TO PRINT MY TICKET?












          No. All tickets are 100% mobile!


















            ARE TICKETS REFUNDABLE?












          VCBW tickets are non-refundable. Tickets are transferable and thus can be given away to friends or sold on 3rd party sites. We do not hold any responsibility for tickets that are bought, sold, given away or received privately as there is no way to trace them to the new buyer. 


















            WHAT ABOUT IF IT IS POSTPONED?












          If the event is postponed for any reason, tickets will not be refunded.  All tickets will be valid for the next VCBW.


















            IS THERE A TICKET LIMIT?












          No, there is not.


















            HOW ARE TICKETS DELIVERED?  












          Tickets are all mobile tickets. Tickets will be will issued 48-hours prior to the event, via email/inside your Ticketleader.ca account.


















            ARE THERE TICKETING FEES AND TAX?












          Yes. We use a 3rd party ticketing site and they don’t work for free. The fees have been negotiated for the benefit of our guests and continue to be minimal. Regarding tax, only GST is charged on tickets. 


















            HOW MUCH IS PARKING?












          Parking lots are run by the PNE and thus still to be determined.  But, it is a beer festival so please do not drive to the event. 


















            IS THERE HANDICAP ACCESS AND PARKING?












          Yes. If you require parking for the disabled, there will be spots onsite. There are ramps where needed for wheelchair and more gradual ups and downs where necessary.


















            ARE THERE VOLUNTEER TICKETS AND HOW DO THEY WORK?












          If you would like to volunteer at this event, please contact us using the contact link.


















            WHAT AGE DO I HAVE TO BE TO ATTEND? CAN I BRING MY KIDS?












          Every single person attending has to be 19 years or older, with no exceptions.  Proof of age is required to gain entry. So, you can bring your kids, as long as they are 19 years or older.


















            CAN I BRING MY DOG? 












          Sorry, no pets allowed.


















            Will security will be present at the event?












          As always, the PNE security team will be on hand making sure all runs safe and smoothly at VCBW.No backpacks will be allowed into the event. 


















            ARE OUTSIDE FOOD AND DRINK ALLOWED AT THE EVENT?












          Sorry but no outside food or drink is permitted to enter the premises. You may bring a refillable water bottle inside.


















            DO I HAVE TO WEAR A MASK OR BE VACCINATED?












          Safety is our primary priority and VCBW is committed to hosting a safe event. To help ensure we can move forward, VCBW will follow all local, provincial and federal mandatory requirements with respect to Covid restrictions. VCBW will not implement any additional restrictions. At the time of this being written, masks nor vaccine passports are not required and thus VCBW would not require them.Please read our Health and Safety Protocols for complete details.


















            IS SMOKING PERMITTED AT THIS EVENT?












          Yes, in the designated smoking area only.














































